[Patient] How much fluid should I drink each day?
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for around 8 cups (64 oz) of fluids daily to help manage your heart failure.
[Patient] Can I drink any type of fluids?
[Healthcare Educator] Focus on water, herbal tea, and low-sugar drinks to prevent fluid overload.
[Patient] How do I track my fluid intake?
[Healthcare Educator] Use a diary or designated containers to measure fluids and monitor intake throughout the day.
[Patient] What if I can't afford medications?
[Healthcare Educator] Connect with local health clinics or social services for assistance in accessing necessary medications.
[Patient] How can I prevent complications?
[Healthcare Educator] Monitoring your fluid intake can help prevent complications and improve your overall health outcomes.